==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sequel
<hw>Se"quel</hw> <pr>(s⟦emac⟧"kw⟦ecr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sequela</ets>, fr. <ets>sequit</ets> to follow: cf. F.
<ets>s⟦eacute⟧quelle</ets> a following. See <er>Sue</er> to
follow.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which follows; a succeeding part;
continuation; <as>as, the <ex>sequel</ex> of a man's advantures or
history</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, let me say no more!⟦br⟧
Gather the <qex>sequel</qex> by that went before.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Consequence; event; effect; result; <as>as, let the
sun cease, fail, or swerve, and the <ex>sequel</ex> would be
ruin</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Conclusion; inference.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Whitgift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sequela</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
